Build a Tic-Tac-Toe (X/O) web app as a single self-contained HTML file
(HTML + CSS + JavaScript, no external dependencies or build step).

Requirements:
- 3x3 grid, two human players alternating X and O, X goes first
- Clicking an empty cell places the current player's mark; filled cells can't be overwritten
- Detect and announce a win (all 8 lines) and highlight the winning three cells
- Detect a draw when the board is full with no winner
- Show whose turn it is, and the result when the game ends
- A "Reset" button that clears the board and starts a new game
- Clean, responsive layout that works on mobile and desktop

Don't use any frameworks or CDNs — plain vanilla JS. The whole thing should
run by opening the file in a browser.